A flood warning has been issued for Gauteng. The Weather Service says heavy rains can be expected throughout the weekend. Emergency Services are on high alert. eNCA's Lindokuhle Xulu brings you the latest details. Courtesy #DStv403 #eNCA JOHANNESBURG - Johannesburg Emergency Services are on high alert as heavy rains are expected to persist throughout the weekend. The rain has caused widespread flooding in some parts of Johannesburg, with Bryanston and Douglasdale mostly affected. READ: KZN floods | Tough times ahead for Ladysmith residents Motorists are urged to be extra cautious while driving due to wet and slippery conditions. The water rescue and disaster management teams are also on high alert. The South African Weather Service has issued a level 4 yellow warning for disruptive and heavy rain in Gauteng, western Mpumalanga, and the western Bushveld of Limpopo. READ: KZN flood relief packages distributed At the same time, KwaZulu-Natal disaster management teams are on high alert as heavy downpours are expected to batter parts of the province. The KZN Cooperative Government Department says some parts of the province have already experienced heavy rains. Disaster management teams are closely monitoring the inclement weather. Communities living in low lying areas are urged to take the necessary precautions. Motorists are warned against driving through flooded areas. Tshwane motorists are being urged to avoid some roads and low-lying bridges in the metro. Severe storms and flooding are causing havoc. The Metro's Emergency Services spokesperson, Charles Mabaso, provides the latest details. Courtesy #DStv403 #eNCA